---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: 'O.M. Binmsaad — Integration Engineer & Author',
  description: 'O.M. Binmsaad is an integration engineer with 8+ years of experience building SaaS API integrations. Author of the API Integration Hub documentation.',
  keywords: ['api integration hub author', 'o.m. binmsaad', 'integration engineer', 'saas api documentation'],
};
---

<BaseLayout {frontmatter}>
  <main>
    <h1>O.M. Binmsaad</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Integration Engineer &amp; Author, API Integration Hub</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>I'm an integration engineer with 8+ years of experience building and troubleshooting SaaS API integrations in production environments. My work has focused on the data layer between CRM platforms and marketing automation tools — the exact place where APIs collide and errors emerge.</p>
      <p>Over the years, I've built integrations between Salesforce, HubSpot, Pipedrive, Zoho CRM, Mailchimp, ActiveCampaign, Slack, and dozens of other tools. Every integration I've built has taught me something new about how APIs fail — and how to fix them.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Certifications & Expertise</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Salesforce Certified Platform Developer</strong> — Apex, REST/SOAP APIs, platform events</li>
        <li><strong>HubSpot API Partner Program</strong> — CRM objects, webhooks, OAuth 2.0 flows</li>
        <li><strong>Zapier Certified Expert</strong> — Multi-step Zaps, custom code steps, error handling</li>
        <li><strong>Make (Integromat) Certified Partner</strong> — Complex multi-module scenarios, error handlers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Areas of Specialization</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>OAuth 2.0 authentication flows and automated token refresh</li>
        <li>Rate limit handling and retry strategies across distributed systems</li>
        <li>Webhook verification, payload validation, and idempotency</li>
        <li>Field mapping and data type coercion between tools</li>
        <li>Silent failure detection — errors that produce no HTTP status but corrupt data</li>
        <li>API version migrations and breaking change management</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why I Built API Integration Hub</h2>
      <p>Official API documentation tells you how an API <em>should</em> work. It rarely covers what happens when two APIs interact — the edge cases, silent failures, and cross-tool errors that only surface in production under real load.</p>
      <p>I started API Integration Hub to document these integration-layer failures. Every guide on this site is based on errors I've personally encountered, debugged, and fixed. This is the documentation I wish existed when I was building integrations at 2 AM.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Independence</h2>
      <p>API Integration Hub is my independent project. I am not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by any of the tools I document. My opinions and recommendations are based solely on production experience.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Found an error or have a suggestion? <a href="/contact">Reach out here</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'O.M. Binmsaad',
    jobTitle: 'Integration Engineer',
    description: 'Integration engineer with 8+ years of experience building SaaS API integrations.',
    url: new URL('/author', Astro.url.origin).href,
    knowsAbout: [
      'API Integration',
      'OAuth 2.0',
      'Webhooks',
      'SaaS Integration',
      'Salesforce API',
      'HubSpot API',
      'Slack API',
      'Zapier',
      'Make Integromat',
    ],
    hasCredential: [
      { '@type': 'EducationalOccupationalCredential', name: 'Salesforce Certified Platform Developer' },
      { '@type': 'EducationalOccupationalCredential', name: 'HubSpot API Partner Program' },
      { '@type': 'EducationalOccupationalCredential', name: 'Zapier Certified Expert' },
      { '@type': 'EducationalOccupationalCredential', name: 'Make (Integromat) Certified Partner' },
    ],
  })} />
</BaseLayout>
